data.meta_description: The Jackson County Development Committee is at work every day to match the best workers, sites, incentives, and infrastructure with the businesses growing in and moving to Jackson County. Contact us today to see how we can help.
data.text:
The Jackson County Economic Development Committee is at work every day to match the best workers, sites, incentives, and infrastructure with the businesses growing in and moving to Jackson County. Contact us today to see how we can help.

Darwin Gilmore named JCEDC President

The Jackson County Economic Development Council’s Executive Board has selected Marianna native Darwin Gilmore as their new President/CEO. Gilmore brings a wealth of knowledge to the Council, having been in the family business where he and his wife, Cheri, owned and operated two separate manufacturing companies, which turned into a 15-plus year exposure to small business management.

Chick-fil-A planned for Marianna

Chick-fil-A plans to build one of its restaurants in Marianna and it could be open by the end of 2022 or the start of 2023 if all goes as planned.

The Jackson County Economic Development Committee, Inc. Board of Directors meets quarterly (January, April, July, October) on the 4th Monday of the Month at 12:00 p.m. CST at the Historic Joseph Russ House located at 4318 Lafayette Street, Marianna, FL 32446.

The Jackson County Economic Development Committee, Inc. Executive Board meets monthly on the 2nd Monday of the Month at 11:00 a.m. cst in the same location.

In the case of a holiday the meeting is moved to the prior Monday.
